Manage the environment lifecycle

Usage:
  git-hop env [command]

Available Commands:
  gc          Garbage collect orphaned dependencies
  generate    Generate environment files (.env, override) for the current worktree
  start       Start the environment services
  stop        Stop the environment services

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for env

Global Flags:
      --config string   config file (default is $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/git-hop/config.json)
      --dry-run         preview changes without applying
      --force           bypass safety checks
  -g, --global          use global hopspace in $GIT_HOP_DATA_HOME (default: local)
      --json            output in JSON format
      --porcelain       machine-readable output
  -q, --quiet           suppress output
  -v, --verbose         verbose output

Use "git-hop env [command] --help" for more information about a command.
